# Version bump on commit

Whenever you create a git commit in this repo:

1. Bump `client/package.json` `version` before committing (semver).
2. Patch (`0.2.1` → `0.2.2`) for fixes and small changes.
3. Minor (`0.2.x` → `0.3.0`) for user-facing features.
4. Include the version file in the same commit.
5. Mention the new version in the commit message when natural (e.g. `fix call hangup (v0.2.2)`).
